      "text" : "compared centaur with aeon - 'both run agents that you don't watch, but they sit at opposite ends of the deployment spectrum.' \n\n- Aeon maximizes autonomy per operator at the cost of isolation — your GITHUB_TOKEN and API keys live in the same env the skill runs in, and there is no sandbox between a skill and your secrets. Acceptable because it's your repo running your skills.\n- Centaur maximizes isolation and auditability at the cost of infra weight — a Kubernetes cluster, Postgres, iron-proxy, and Slack app just to run one agent turn. Acceptable because multiple humans share it and need credential boundaries + replayable transcripts.\n\nvery interesting design overall"
