      "created_at" : "Fri Apr 17 22:01:22 +0000 2026",
      "text" : "everything i've shipped this week:\n\n@miroshark_ - agent simulations\n\nthe goal: simulations you can actually ship findings from. not demos. not vibes. real knowledge extraction from agent runs.\n\n- director mode — inject events mid-simulation. breaking news, policy changes, whatever. watch agents update beliefs in real time instead of running static scenarios.\n- agent interaction network graph — finally see the social topology. who talks to whom, who's isolated, who's the broker. emergent structure becomes legible.\n- quality diagnostics w/ health badge — every run gets scored. actionable suggestions when a sim is degenerate. no more squinting at logs to figure out if a run was useful.\n- post-sim trace-grounded interviews — ask any agent why they did what they did. answers are grounded in their actual trace, not hallucinated post-hoc. the \"why\" is finally interrogable.\n- prediction resolution + accuracy tracking — agents make predictions, predictions get resolved, accuracy gets tracked across runs. calibration as a first-class metric.\n- belief drift chart w/ per-round stance distribution — watch opinions shift round by round. aggregate view across the population. polarization, convergence, capture — all visible.\n- one-click article generator — simulation → publishable writeup. results come out as something you can share, not a json dump.\n- history search / filter — past runs are now browsable. you can actually build on prior work instead of every sim being an island.\n- browser push notifications on completion — long runs notify you when done. obvious, was missing, now fixed.\n- multi-model routing + openrouter observability — different agents can use different models. full visibility into token spend + attribution headers correct so providers see proper routing.\n- NER extraction quality fixes — garbage entity filtering. cleaner knowledge graphs out of every run.\n- path traversal hardening — sanitized simulation_id in all path ops. security hygiene.\n\n@aeonframework - autonomous agent framework\n\nthe goal: aeon isnt a silo anymore. its infra. any framework should be able to plug in.\n\n- A2A protocol gateway — all 91 skills exposed to any AI agent framework via the A2A protocol. aeon becomes a capability layer, not a walled garden.\n- MCP skill adaptor — every aeon skill automatically becomes a claude tool. instant integration with anything mcp-aware.\n- auto-merge skill — green PRs merge themselves. closes the self-improve loop — aeon can now actually ship its own improvements without a human in every seat.\n- skill version tracking + provenance lock — every skill carries its origin + version. upstream drift detection flags when sources change. no silent rot.\n- gate skills.lock auto-advance behind human confirmation — the self-improve loop has a safety rail. agent cant unilaterally promote itself past checks.\n- syndicate-article skill — one-shot devto cross-posting. results flow outward automatically.\n- monitor-kalshi skill — track prediction markets natively. aeon agents can now watch kalshi markets as a data source.\n- email notifications via sendgrid — agents can ping you out of band. another channel beyond the terminal.\n- skill dependency graph — mermaid map of all 91 skills + how they connect. the framework is finally visible as a system, not a pile of files.\n- opus 4.6 → 4.7 default — latest model across the board.\n- eval-audit + xai prefetch hardening — error logging ported from aaron fork. failures are louder and more diagnosable.\n- fetch-tweets pipeline hardened — ported miroshark's hardened version. fewer silent drops.\n- messages.yml injection hardening — user messages cant execute arbitrary script via yaml. security fix.\n- 25 new skills merged from fork — aaron fork → main. 2-workflow simplification + quality fixes came along.\n- README overhaul — 768 lines → 496. autonomy comparison table vs claude code / hermes / openclaw. repositioned: \"the most autonomous agent framework.\"\ntheme of the week\n\nnext week bigger"
